02/07/2010
By Linda Karadaku for Southeast European Times in Pristina.
Kosovo, Macedonia, Montenegro and Albania stand united on energy issues, the economy, infrastructure, the battle against crime and other issues, as proof of their readiness for eventual EU integration. 
Prevalla, Kosovo, hosted a summit where the leaders announced the opening of a mini-Schengen zone among their states. They also agreed on furthering relations through co-operation and dialogue. 
